data.name: Meet and Greet NPOs
data.description: Ballroom A. Come to hear our wonderful NPOs and hear about the causes they're advocating for. This is a great space in which to find your next project idea.

data.description: Ballroom A

data.name: Workshop: API Development and Testing by Bit Project
data.description: Ballroom A. In this workshop, you will learn how to use APIs in your projects. APIs allow for easy communication between projects and developer tools. You will be testing mock APIs and also get a chance to interact with real existing developer APIs, all through the developer tool Postman.

data.description: Makerspace

data.description: Ballroom A

data.description: Ballroom A

data.name: Workshop: Build Your Virtual Reality Game by Student Startup Center
data.description: Makerspace

data.name: Workshop: Intro to Frontend Development with Vue.js by Hao Huang
data.description: Ballroom A. In this workshop, you will learn the basics of Vue.js, the most popular frontend framework, and how you can use Vue to create reusable components to speed up future development. We will also do a live coding example on how to create a simple to-do list app using Vue.

data.name: Workshop: Personal Branding Workshop by #include
data.description: Ballroom B. include will be hosting a workshop on career guidance and development. We will be going over forming your personal brand online and offline, as well as utilizing and improving your LinkedIn profile. We will also provide tips for building your resume, touch on how you can leverage HackDavis in your professional network, and end with a basic LaTeX tutorial as a means of designing your resume! We hope to see you there!

data.name: MLH Cup Stacking
data.description: Games Area

data.name: Resume Feedback Session
data.description: Networking Space. Get detailed feedback on your resumes & how you can improve them from our set of wonderful HD alumni.

data.name: Workshop: Intro to Android Mobile Development by DSC
data.description: Ballroom A

data.name: Workshop: Introduction to Unity by Game Dev Club
data.description: Ballroom B. Come to our workshop to gain a foundational understanding of what Unity can be used for and how to use it in your projects. A sample project will be provided and we will be learning core concepts with it. We will be covering some of the most important concepts and by the end of the workshop, you will be able to make your own games.

data.name: Workshop: Machine Learning for Beginners by AI Society
data.description: Ballroom A. In this workshop, you will learn how to build neural networks- computer systems inspired by the human brain. Learn how to build neural networks 3 different ways using Tensorflow/Keras.

data.name: Workshop: UI/UX Design for Hackathons by DCSC and WiCS
data.description: Ballroom B. Davis Computer Science Club and Davis Women in Computer Science are proud to present their “UI/UX Design for Hackathons” workshop! We will go over the basics of UX design, how you can incorporate design thinking into creating a meaningful product, and the basics of using Adobe XD to design, prototype, and eventually handoff to developers!
